===Domestic trophies=== {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * European: **[[European Rugby Champions Cup]] &ndash; a competition involving leading club, regional, and provincial teams from England, France, Ireland, Italy, Scotland, and Wales **[[European Challenge Cup]] &ndash; the second-tier competition to the European Rugby Champions Cup **[[European Shield]] &ndash; a defunct repechage tournament for teams knocked out in the first round of the European Challenge Cup (no longer awarded) **[[Heineken Cup]] (no longer awarded) * France: **[[Bouclier de Brennus]] &ndash; to the champions of the [[Top 14]] league * Great Britain and Ireland: **[[Anglo-Welsh Cup]] &ndash; (aka LV Cup, a cup competition for English and Welsh top-level club teams) **[[British and Irish Cup]] &ndash; a cup competition for British and Irish semi-pro club teams * New Zealand: **[[ITM Cup]] &ndash; New Zealand's annual professional domestic competition **[[Meads Cup]] &ndash; a cup played for between provincial teams during the [[Heartland Championship]], the second-tier domestic league **[[Heartland Championship|Lochore Cup]] &ndash; the secondary trophy in the Heartland Championship **[[Ranfurly Shield]] &ndash; a trophy between provincial teams * South Africa: **[[Currie Cup]] &ndash; South Africa's premier domestic competition * Southern Hemisphere: **[[Super Rugby Trophy]] &ndash; to the winners of the [[Super Rugby]] competition {{div col end}}
