===Posthumous=== Many prizes, medals, and awards can be granted [[Wiktionary:posthumously|posthumously]]. Australian actor [[Heath Ledger]], for example, won [[List of awards and nominations received by Heath Ledger|many awards]] after his death in 2008. Military decorations, such as the [[Medal of Honor]], are often given posthumously.
Less commonly, certain prizes, medals, and awards are granted ''only'' posthumously, especially those that honor people who died in service to a particular cause. Such awards include: *[[Dag Hammarskjöld Medal]] &ndash; to military personnel, police, or civilians who lost their lives while serving in a [[United Nations]] [[peacekeeping operation]]
