{{Costa Rican censuses}} The '''National Institute of Statistics and Census''' of [[Costa Rica]] (''Instituto Nacional de Estadística y Censos de Costa Rica'', or ''INEC'', in Spanish) is the governmental institution entrusted with the running of [[census]]es and official [[statistical survey|surveys]] in the country. Its main office is located in [[San José, Costa Rica|San José]].
== History == INEC was first called ''Oficina Central de Estadística'' about its foundation in 1861. Later, in 1951, it was called ''Dirección General de Estadística y Censos'', until 1998, when INEC was its legal name. INEC ran its first census in 1864, and the latest was the [[Costa Rica 2011 Census|10th population and the 6th dwellings census]], held in June 2011.
== Censuses in Costa Rica == * '''1864'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1864/index.htm First Population Census]. * '''1883'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1883/index.htm Second Population Census]. * '''1892'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1892/index.htm Third Population Census]. * '''1927'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1927/index.htm Fourth Population Census]. * '''1950'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1950/index.htm Fifth Population Census]. * '''1963'''. [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr/bvp/censos/1963/index.htm Sixth Population Census]. * '''1973'''. Seventh Population Census. Available at [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr CCP]. * '''1984'''. Eighth Population Census. Available at [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr CCP]. * '''2000'''. [[Costa Rica 2000 Census|Ninth Population Census]]. Available at [http://ccp.ucr.ac.cr CCP]. * '''2011'''. [[Costa Rica 2011 Census|Tenth Population Census]].
