'''Ngulgule''' is an ethnic group of [[South Sudan]]<ref>[http://www.gurtong.net/Peoples/PeoplesProfiles/Ngulngule/tabid/222/Default.aspx Gurtong Peace Project]</ref>  living just north of the confluence of the Sopo and Boro rivers.<ref name=EthnologueNgulgule>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=njl Ethnologue: "Njalgulgule - A language of Sudan"] retrieved February 5, 2013</ref> They are one of seven distinct ethnicities comprising the [[Daju people]]. They speak [[Njalgulgule language|Njalgulgule]], a Nilo-Saharan language. Most of them are Muslims. The population of this group is 900.<ref name=EthnologueNgulgule />

